#let title = [Separate Data from Functions]

#let body = [
DIZZY is intentionally a mostly functional paradigm. Data (commands, events, models, and query IO) and functions (procedures, policies, projections, and queriers) are explicitly separated. This is fundamentally different from the traditional Object Oriented Paradigm that traditional DDD is based upon.

This separation is what enables various components of the full DIZZY system to be deployed independently.
]
